UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2417
1 WHEREAS, the MAHA movement calls for transparent, science-based health
2 policies and recommendations that are in the best interest of the public and are free from
3 undue corporate influence;
4 NOW, THEREFORE,
5 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
6 Kentucky, the House of Representatives concurring therein:
7 Section 1. The General Assembly supports the goals of the Make America
8 Healthy Again movement, and in doing so:
9 (1) Supports policies that increase access to clean, whole foods across Kentucky
10 to enhance nutrition and reduce diet-related diseases;
11 (2) Encourages access to local, fresh produce in schools, communities, and
12 markets through initiatives like farmers' markets and farm-to-school programs;
13 (3) Encourages public health efforts to educate Kentuckians on healthy living,
14 good nutrition, and chronic disease prevention;
15 (4) Urges state and local health agencies to collaborate with schools and
16 community organizations to expand public health programs that focus on empowering
17 individuals and families with knowledge on how to manage their own health through
18 good nutrition, regular physical activity, and avoidance of harmful substances;
19 (5) Urges legislative and regulatory updates to align agricultural and health
20 policies, including:
21 (a) Creating incentives for the production and consumption of nutritious foods in
22 Kentucky;
23 (b) Encouraging Kentuckians to make healthy food choices, including reducing
24 reliance on highly processed, high sugar products, through education and policy
25 incentives; and
26 (c) Addressing environmental health risks to improve overall public health
27 outcomes;
Page 2 of 5
XXXX 3/25/2026 12:49 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2417
1 (6) Recognizes the role of immunity as a factor in public health policy alongside
2 other preventive measures; and
3 (7) Encourages state health officials to consider evidence of immunity from prior
4 illness as part of broader health guidelines and emergency response plans.
5 Section 2. (1) The Legislative Research Commission shall establish the
6 Make America Healthy Again Kentucky Task Force.
7 (2) The duties of the task force shall include but are not limited to:
8 (a) Exploring ways that Kentucky can integrate the MAHA movement principles
9 into state laws, policies, and programs to improve the overall health of Kentuckians,
10 including the "Take Back Your Health" and "Eat Real Food" initiatives;
11 (b) Reviewing strategies that Kentucky may use to improve health outcomes
12 through:
13 1. Encouraging dietary and lifestyle changes;
14 2. Expanding public awareness efforts on healthy nutrition and lifestyles;
15 3. Reducing public exposure to environmental toxins; and
16 4. Increasing public awareness and input into state health policies; and
17 (c) Building on recommendations from the 2025 Make America Healthy Again
18 Kentucky Task Force relating to:
19 1. Healthy food initiatives including:
20 a. The Food is Medicine collaboration of the Kentucky Department of
21 Agriculture and the Kentucky Hospital Association;
22 b. The purchase of healthy foods with Supplemental Nutritional Assistance
23 Program (SNAP) dollars and the connections between SNAP and the Medicaid program;
24 c. Improvement of healthy meals and nutrition education in schools; and
25 d. Increased access to foods that are not ultra-processed;
26 2. Physical health and wellness including:
27 a. Strengthening of school physical education requirements;
Page 3 of 5
XXXX 3/25/2026 12:49 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2417
1 b. Improving local school wellness policies; and
2 c. Strengthening efforts to improve the overall health of Kentuckians; and
3 3. Functional medicine including:
4 a. Increasing health care provider education on integrating nutrition and diet
5 strategies for improving health outcomes for chronic disease;
6 b. Improving health insurance coverage of functional medicine programs; and
7 c. Encouraging the integration of functional medicine principles in preventative
8 health initiatives.
9 Section 3. The Make America Healthy Again Kentucky Task Force shall be
10 composed of the following members with final membership of the task force being
11 subject to the consideration and approval of the Legislative Research Commission:
12 (1) Three members of the House of Representatives appointed by the Speaker of
13 the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be designated by the Speaker of the
14 House of Representatives as a co-chair of the task force;
15 (2) Three members of the Senate appointed by the President of the Senate, one of
16 whom shall be designated by the President of the Senate as a co-chair of the task force;
17 (3) One member of the House of Representatives appointed by the Minority Floor
18 Leader of the House; and
19 (4) One member of the Senate appointed by the Minority Floor Leader of the
20 Senate.
21 Section 4. The Make America Healthy Again Kentucky Task Force shall at a
22 minimum meet monthly during the 2026 Interim of the General Assembly and shall
23 submit recommendations to the Governor and to the Legislative Research Commission
24 for referral to the Interim Joint Committee on Families and Children by December 1,
25 2026.
26 Section 5. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
27 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
Page 4 of 5
